attachments.title: City of Cranes (extract)
attachments.text:
Dir.: Eva Weber
Ed.: Ariadna Fatjo-Vilas 
2006 12'

Cranes dominate our skylines, yet few people ever notice them. Spending most of their time alone up in the crane, crane operators seem to merge with their machines, becoming invisible to passers-by. City of Cranes takes the viewer hundreds of feet above the ground to hear the insights of crane operators, and see a glimpse of the poetic, mesmerizing world of cranes.

- TX Channel 4, PBS
-Won the Hellenic Red Cross Audience Award for best Foreign Short at the Thessaloniki Documentary Film Festival 08
- Won the Jury Award for Best Short at Full Frame Documentary Film Festival in Durham, N.C. 08
- Slamdance’08
